inconspicuous tubercle dorsally and C-shaped compound eyes laterally (
Fig. 34
). Posteriolateral margins of eyes without enlarged alveoli of supraocular bristles on both sides. Eyes separated, eye bridge divided by one facet diameter (
Fig. 34
) and formed by 3 facet rows (
Fig. 35
). Ratio of distances of apices of eyes (tangential points) to facet diameter 10:1. Dorsal and ventral apices of eyes are almost of the same size, only ventrally a little narrower. Hairs of frons are sporadic (
Figs. 34, 35
). Scar patch of frontoclypeus as well as above the upper apices of eyes is continuous, not divided in vertical axis by a median scar-free band. Antennae incomplete (
Fig. 42
). Scape almost cylindrical, 2.2 times as long as pedicel which is globular. Basal flagellomeres pitcher-shaped, bulbose part asymmetrical in horizontal axis (against postpedicel), necks (internodes) represent 1/3 of the length of article. Ascoids simple, digitate, paired (
Fig. 42
). Mouthparts not extending beyond basal palp segment (
Fig. 34
). Labellum bulbose, with digital protuberances in between (
Fig. 43
), miniature spines between both lobes are not developed. Length ratio of maxillary palps 1.0:1.1:1.3:1.5, segment 4 not annulate (
Fig. 36
). Ratio of maximum length of cibarium to length of epipharynx 1.3:1 (
Fig. 34
), labrum pointed (
Fig. 49
).

Male genitalia. Ejaculatory apodeme longly U-shaped with three conspicuously sclerotised ribs distally (
Fig.40
). Aedeagal complex flanked by jointed needle-shaped moveable appendages approximately of the same length as aedeagus which is racquet-shaped, clearly symmetrical, with conspicuous flaps on both sides. Gonostyli gradually tapering to tips, 1.2 times as long as gonocoxites which are cylindrical and a little bent (
Figs. 39
, 
44
). Epandrium trapezoidal, with two patches of hairs distally (
Figs. 51, 52
), central aperture doubled. Ventral plate was not observed. Hypandrium stripe-shaped, inconspicuously strengthened medially (
Figs. 40
, 
52
). Hypoproct and epiproct are tongue-shaped, both parts haired (
Fig. 51
). Hypoproct is almost triangular, with miniature microsetae, epiproct approximately semicircular, longly setose. Epandrial clasping lobes almost cylindrical, a little strengthened basally, haired and inconspicuously bent (
Figs. 51, 52
), 1.8 times as long as epandrium (
Fig. 52
), with 12–13 tenacula, frayed apically (
Fig. 51
).

Differential diagnosis
. 

Iranotelmatoscopus kenyensis

sp. nov.
is morphologically similar to 

I. hajiabadi
Ježek, 1987

, however, male characters are quite different: index of distance of tangential points of apices of eyes to facet diameter 10.0 (
Fig. 34
), length ratio of maxillary palps 1.0:1.1:1.3:1.5 (
Fig. 36
), last segment of maxillary palp not annulate (
Fig. 36
), medial wing angle 180° (
Fig. 57
), wing index 2.6 (
Fig. 57
), sclerotized ribs of ejaculatory apodeme distally in number three (
Fig. 40
), conspicuous flaps on both sides of racquet-shaped aedeagus developed (
Figs. 40
, 
45
) and doubled epandrial aperture (
Fig. 51
). Female characters are as follows (see only 
Fig. 47
): digital sensory organ of subgenital plate developed, performed trapezoidal tablet of subgenital plate not developed, lateral inner lobuli distally oblong-shaped and proximal stils of genital chamber from dorsal view in number two.
